Actions.ActionName: Get and format all macro-related UUID stuff
Actions.Text: set apscDone1 to falseset loopCount1 to 0repeat until apscDone1 is true or loopCount1 is 15	try				-- Initialize lists		set idList to {}		set UUIDList to {}		set NameList to {}		set StatusList to {}				-- Get all macros		tell application "Keyboard Maestro"			set macroCount to count macros			repeat with i from 1 to macroCount				set thisMacro to macro i				set end of idList to id of macro group of thisMacro				set end of UUIDList to id of thisMacro				set end of NameList to name of thisMacro				set end of StatusList to enabled of thisMacro			end repeat		end tell				-- Combine the lists		set combinedList to {}		set itemCount to (count of idList)		repeat with i from 1 to itemCount			set combinedItem to item i of idList & "‚Üêüî∏‚Üí" & item i of UUIDList & "‚Üêüî∏‚Üí" & item i of NameList & "‚Üêüî∏‚Üí" & item i of StatusList			set end of combinedList to combinedItem		end repeat				-- Convert the combined list to text		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to linefeed		set combinedText to combinedList as text				set kmInst to system attribute "KMINSTANCE"				tell application "Keyboard Maestro Engine"			setvariable "instance_UUIDmacros" instance kmInst to (combinedList as text)		end tell				set apscDone1 to true	on error		set apscDone1 to false		set loopCount1 to loopCount1 + 1	end tryend repeat

Actions.ActionName: Save macro-related UUID data to file
Get and format all group-related UUID stuff
Actions.Text: set apscDone1 to falseset loopCount1 to 0repeat until apscDone1 is true or loopCount1 is 15	try				--if application "Keyboard Maestro Engine" is not running then tell application "Keyboard Maestro Engine" to launch				tell application "Keyboard Maestro"			set groupUUID to get id of macro groups			set groupName to get name of macro groups			set groupStatus to get enabled of macro groups		end tell				set combinedList to {}				repeat with i from 1 to count of groupUUID			set groupUUIDText to (item i of groupUUID) as text			set groupNameText to (item i of groupName) as text			set groupStatusText to (item i of groupStatus) as text			set combinedRecord to groupUUIDText & "‚Üêüî∏‚Üí" & groupNameText & "‚Üêüî∏‚Üí" & groupStatusText & linefeed			set end of combinedList to combinedRecord		end repeat				set kmInst to system attribute "KMINSTANCE"				tell application "Keyboard Maestro Engine"			setvariable "instance_UUIDgroups" instance kmInst to (combinedList as text)		end tell				set apscDone1 to true			on error		set apscDone1 to false		set loopCount1 to loopCount1 + 1	end tryend repeat

Remove / and : from names - to make Finder matching much simpler
Clear large instance variables after use, no need to keep them around
